issue_comments.body:
@AkashKumar7902 Per the guidance at https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#choosing-a-good-first-issue, please provide an explanation of what your PR will do (with names of files you're changing, what you plan to change in each file, etc.). If it looks good, we can assign you to this issue.

Please also follow the other instructions on that wiki page if you have not yet done so. Thanks!

@DhairyaMajmudar Let's leave this particular issue for newer contributors. I think it would be better if you took slightly harder issues going forward (e.g. the ones in https://github.com/orgs/oppia/projects/3/views/8) so that you can expand your skillset.

@Madhu-mac Per the guidance at https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#choosing-a-good-first-issue, please provide an explanation of what your PR will do (with names of files you're changing, what you plan to change in each file, etc.). If it looks good, we can assign you to this issue.

Please also follow the other instructions on that wiki page if you have not yet done so. Thanks!

Note that we would want a PR to be made shortly after the issue is claimed, to prevent issue assignments from going stale. So please ensure that you have everything ready locally before posting the above and claiming it.
